class Solution {
    public boolean canChange(String start, String target) {
        int n = start.length();
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        while (i < n || j < n) {
            while (i < n && start.charAt(i) == '_') i++;
            while (j < n && target.charAt(j) == '_') j++;
            if (i == n && j == n) return true;
            if (i == n || j == n) return false;
            if (start.charAt(i) != target.charAt(j)) return false;
            if (start.charAt(i) == 'L' && i < j) return false;
            if (start.charAt(i) == 'R' && i > j) return false;
            i++; j++;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Two-pointer sweep: non-underscore characters must appear in identical order; each 'L' in target must be at same or leftward position relative to start, each 'R' must be at same or rightward. Single pass, constant memory.

